Fordyce spots (Fordyce granules) are enlarged, slightly raised sebaceous (oil) glands that appear in hairless areas of your skin. They commonly appear around the edges of your lips (vermillion border)Fordyce spots are benign (not cancerous.
Lip blushing can help disguise the spots . 
This picture is before and healed lipblushing. Now she has a more uniform color and defined lips 👄 .
